    <font size="2"> <i>February 20, 2002---Japan&#39;s Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry (METI), said this week that it plans to oblige power retailers from fiscal 2003 and sell certain amounts of energy generated by solar, wind and other types of renewable sources.</i><br>
    <br>
    According to a draft bill made available Monday, METI aims to obtain cabinet approval on March 1 to submit to the ongoing Diet session a bill on special measures for the use of new energy by power utilities, ministry officials said.
