    </font></b><br>
    <font size="2"> <i>February 19, 2002---With the state in the throes of electricity deregulation, falling natural gas prices and the Enron breakdown Dallas based utility TXU appears to be the clam at the eye of the storm. As utilities stocks, long considered the investment of choice for widows and orphans, continue to fall TXU trades at near its 52 week high of $51.50 per share.</i><br>
