    </font></b><br>
    <font size="2"> <i>February 18, 2002---The latest in the long stream of lawsuits surrounding the Enron mess comes from the law firm Glancy & Binkow LLP. The firm announced last Friday a shareholder class action lawsuit against J.P. Morgan Chase & Co, alleging that the No. 2 U.S. bank holding company did not initially divulge the full extent of its exposure to failed energy trader Enron Corp.</i><br>
    <br>
    The law firm in its complaint charged that ``material omissions and the dissemination of materially false and misleading statements&#39;&#39; related to Enron artificially inflated the bank&#39;s stock price. 
<p>
