        <font size="3" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b><font color="#333399"> Mirant Set to Sell Off $1.6 Billion in Assets, Strengthen Balance Sheet 
    </font></b><br>
    <font size="2"> <i>February 15, 2002---Ray Hill, CFO of Mirant Corp., told an audience of investors attending a conference in New York yesterday, that the company’s plan to strengthen its balance sheet with $1.6 billion in asset sales is on track. Hill reported that $300 million worth of asset sales is “very well advanced” and will be completed in the next couple of months as the company moves to restore investor confidence in the wake of Enron’s collapse.</i><br>
    <br>
